Chemistry

Chemistry looks different on the surface but has its own invariants.

Atoms rearrange.

Mass is conserved.

Charge is conserved.

Bonds change.

Properties emerge.

The interesting question becomes:

Which properties survive reaction pathways?

Rather than memorizing reactions individually, you search for conserved structure.

