Biology

Evolution is almost entirely transformation.

Genes mutate.

Proteins fold.

Species diverge.

Yet certain architectures persist for hundreds of millions of years because they solve recurring problems.

The Ariadne thread might be:

Functional constraint.

Not every structure survives.

Only the ones compatible with reality.

